        "created_at": "2019-01-18T00:37:11.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"7\" data-topic=\"149055\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>any thoughts on ebaupins vs perrieres for current drinking?  I was thinking the lieu dit may be more ready.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I\u2019ve never tried the Ebaupins, and it looks like he produced one from 2008-2013. I\u2019ve had his SA Perrieres in 14 and 15, and he appears to have a good source of grapes for that vineyard. 2013 was a difficult vintage for PYCM. My favorite SA from the vintage is the En Remilly and if you can find it the En Remilly Cuvee Nicholas et Mathis.</p>",
